From: Florent Revest <revestflo@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 6 Jun 2026 09:40:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] icnss2: register cnss-genl family for ADRASTEA too
Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [aurora-specific HW glue]

cnss-daemon's initialize_cld80211() resolves a generic-netlink family
named "cnss-genl" (mcast group "cnss-genl-grp") to talk to icnss/cnss
platform drivers. Pixel Watch 2 (aurora) probes via DT compatible
"qcom,icnss" which maps to ADRASTEA_DEVICE_ID, so the existing
icnss_genl_init() / icnss_genl_exit() calls -- gated behind
WCN6750/WCN6450 -- are skipped and "cnss-genl" never appears in the
kernel's family table.

cnss-daemon therefore logs "Couldn't resolve family id" and falls
back to legacy USERSOCK, leaving the WLAN bringup path stuck with
no genl bridge.

Genl-family registration is harmless for any variant, so lift both
calls out of the WCN6750/WCN6450 conditional.

Signed-off-by: Florent Revest <revestflo@gmail.com>

--- a/private/msm-google-modules/wlan/platform/icnss2/main.c
+++ b/private/msm-google-modules/wlan/platform/icnss2/main.c
@@ -4610,10 +4610,6 @@
 		INIT_WORK(&priv->soc_wake_msg_work, icnss_soc_wake_msg_work);
 		INIT_LIST_HEAD(&priv->soc_wake_msg_list);
 
-		ret = icnss_genl_init();
-		if (ret < 0)
-			icnss_pr_err("ICNSS genl init failed %d\n", ret);
-
 		init_completion(&priv->smp2p_soc_wake_wait);
 		icnss_runtime_pm_init(priv);
 		icnss_aop_mbox_init(priv);
@@ -4632,6 +4628,19 @@
 		INIT_WORK(&wpss_loader, icnss_wpss_load);
 	}
 
+	/* The cnss-genl netlink family is what cnss-daemon's
+	 * initialize_cld80211() resolves to talk to icnss/cnss platform
+	 * drivers. Upstream gates icnss_genl_init() on WCN6750/WCN6450,
+	 * but Pixel Watch 2 (aurora) probes via compatible "qcom,icnss"
+	 * which sets device_id = ADRASTEA_DEVICE_ID and skips registration
+	 * entirely -- so cnss-daemon falls back to legacy USERSOCK and the
+	 * platform driver is unreachable. The registration is safe for any
+	 * variant.
+	 */
+	ret = icnss_genl_init();
+	if (ret < 0)
+		icnss_pr_err("ICNSS genl init failed %d\n", ret);
+
 	timer_setup(&priv->recovery_timer,
 		    icnss_recovery_timeout_hdlr, 0);
 
@@ -4737,6 +4746,8 @@
 			destroy_workqueue(priv->soc_wake_wq);
 	}
 
+	icnss_genl_exit();
+
 	class_destroy(priv->icnss_ramdump_class);
 	unregister_chrdev_region(priv->icnss_ramdump_dev, RAMDUMP_NUM_DEVICES);
 
